<plot>We are the organization that thrives in keeping the memory of Grand Master Sifu Sensei Hokkaido Qi alive. His vision to not be "... a stupid boy" was very progressive, yet universal. He constantly shared his Kantianistic view of totalitarianism with everyone he came in contact, always reminding them how "everyone should focus with intensity," because it was universally good for mankind. This film contains footage that was found floating in the west bay of Leyte in the Visayan Islands of the Philippines. After a lengthy restoration period, the filmed segments were compiled, edited and put together by our foundation to preserve the ancient art of M.E.S.P.H.P.K.G.F.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?360429</url></doc>
